{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:16.030Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece and SentencePiece are subword tokenization schemes widely used in BERT-family encoders, T5, multilingual models, and many embedding APIs. Unlike classic BPE's frequency-driven merges, WordPiece uses likelihood-based selection; SentencePiece unifies training and inference with language-agnostic preprocessing. Agent pipelines mixing encoder models (retrieval, reranking) with decoder LLMs often juggle both families."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "WordPiece vs SentencePiece comparison: merge criteria, whitespace handling, and model ecosystems"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece (Google, BERT) iteratively merges pairs that maximize training data likelihood under a language model assumption \u2014 similar to BPE but with a different merge criterion. It typically prefixes continuations with ## in raw token display. SentencePiece (Google) implements BPE and unigram language model tokenization directly on raw Unicode, treating spaces as special symbols (U+2581) without pre-tokenization."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different tokenizers mean the same prompt tokenizes differently across models \u2014 critical when sharing RAG chunks between an embedding model (often SentencePiece or WordPiece) and a generation model (often BPE). Multilingual agents depend on SentencePiece's consistent handling of diverse scripts without language-specific rules."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece: strong for encoders", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 optimized for bidirectional understanding tasks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SentencePiece: language-agnostic", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 no external pretokenizer required"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reversible tokenization", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 decode recovers original text (modulo whitespace markers)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multilingual support", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 T5, mBERT, Llama 2+ use SentencePiece variants"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece ## prefixes and SentencePiece \u2581 markers differ from GPT BPE display"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-tokenizer token counts are not comparable \u2014 budget per model"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Unigram SentencePiece training is slower and more complex than BPE"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mixing tokenizers in one pipeline requires separate vocabularies and ID spaces"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Starting from a character vocabulary, WordPiece evaluates candidate merges by how much they increase corpus likelihood. Continuation pieces are marked (## in BERT vocab files)."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import BertTokenizer\n\ntokenizer = BertTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"bert-base-uncased\")\ntext = \"agentic workflows require careful tokenization\"\nencoded = tokenizer.encode(text, add_special_tokens=True)\nprint(tokenizer.convert_ids_to_tokens(encoded))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SentencePiece"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SentencePiece trains on raw text with spaces replaced by \u2581 (U+2581). Supports BPE and unigram modes. Used by Llama, T5, and many multilingual models."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import sentencepiece as spm\n\n# Illustrative: load a pretrained SentencePiece model\nsp = spm.SentencePieceProcessor(model_file=\"llama.model\")\nids = sp.encode(\"Hello, agent!\", out_type=int)\npieces = sp.encode(\"Hello, agent!\", out_type=str)\nprint(pieces)\nprint(sp.decode(ids))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use WordPiece tokenizers with BERT/RoBERTa-style encoder models for classification and embedding. Use SentencePiece with T5, Llama, and multilingual pipelines. When an agent uses a separate retriever encoder and generator decoder, accept that each has its own tokenizer \u2014 never share token IDs across them."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BERT WordPiece might tokenize \"tokenization\" as [\"token\", \"##ization\"]. SentencePiece might produce [\"\u2581token\", \"ization\"]. The same English sentence can yield 42 tokens on BERT versus 38 on Llama \u2014 affecting cross-model context planning."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A hybrid agent uses a SentencePiece-based embedding model (bge-m3) for multilingual retrieval and a BPE-based GPT-4 class model for generation. RAG passes raw text chunks \u2014 not token IDs \u2014 between stages. Engineers learned this after initially attempting to share tokenized buffers, which failed because ID spaces are incompatible."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feeding BPE token IDs into a WordPiece model's embedding layer"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assuming ## or \u2581 markers are safe to strip without decoding properly"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparing context limits by token count across different tokenizer families"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pass raw text between pipeline stages with different tokenizers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use each model's official tokenizer library for counting and encoding"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For multilingual agents, prefer SentencePiece-trained models with diverse training data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Document which tokenizer each microservice assumes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison with alternatives"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BPE (GPT): frequency merges, dominant in decoder LLMs. WordPiece (BERT): likelihood merges, dominant in encoder models. SentencePiece: unified implementation with BPE/unigram modes and no pretokenization \u2014 preferred for multilingual and T5/Llama ecosystems."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece and SentencePiece are different dialects of subword splitting \u2014 same goal (compress text into a fixed vocabulary), different merge rules and whitespace conventions."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece powers BERT-family encoders; SentencePiece powers T5, Llama, and many multilingual models"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Never share token IDs across models with different tokenizers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SentencePiece handles raw Unicode without language-specific pretokenization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hybrid agent pipelines should pass text, not token IDs, between tokenizer boundaries"}]}]}]}]}}